{
  "stem": "13258.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But there was an organ there, and there was a Gentile organ player.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And so at for Americans, this is a rather strange combination, where on-- on the one side, relatively conservative, but on the other side, a little bit kind of close to reform.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] But on the high holidays, my father, since he was busy working, attended temple mostly only on the holidays.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My maternal grandmother was very Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She was very religious.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, I was afraid to go to her kitchen to not mess up the dishes between the meat and the dairy because that was a no-no.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But when my father went to the temple, as it was done in Germany on the high holidays, he came in a top hat, dark coat, dark suit, and was very formal.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Everybody came, elderly man came in top hats and then changed in the temple to a yarmulke, whatever.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But that-- that was the custom over there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I sang in the-- in the choir for two years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I would not say that I was the first soprano there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I think boys-- I never learned-- I liked music.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "I never learned, really, to read music.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So I was singing more by-- by ear.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But I enjoyed it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I enjoyed it tremendously.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I especially enjoyed the organ, and I fell in love with organ music since then.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, at times, mischievous.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My aunt-- and my mother's sister, at one point, when she came to visit us here in 1970 or '71, said I was a good kid.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was, at times, mischievous, I know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- I remember some of the things only from being told what I did.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
